'''Formula Rossa''' is a [[launched roller coaster]] located at [[Ferrari World]] in [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]]. Manufactured by [[Intamin]], Formula Rossa is the world's [[Fastest roller coasters#Speed rankings|fastest roller coaster]] with a top speed of {{Convert|239|km/h|abbr=on}}.<ref name="RCDB Speed Record Holders">{{cite web|title=Record Holders - Speed|url=http://www.rcdb.com/m/rhr.htm|publisher=Roller Coaster Database|accessdate=6 July 2010|first=Duane|last=Marden}}</ref><ref name="Ferrari Formula Rossa home">{{cite web|title=Formula Rossa|url=http://www.ferrari.com/English/about_ferrari/Theme-Park/Pages/100506_Formula_Rossa.aspx/|publisher=Ferrari|accessdate=6 July 2010|author=Ferrari|date=6 May 2010}}</ref> The coaster train accelerates to its top speed in approximately 5 seconds using a [[Launch track#Hydraulic|hydraulic launch system]] which generates a release velocity similar to that of [[steam catapults]] on an [[aircraft carrier]].{{citation-needed|date=July 2014}} The initial acceleration from standstill reaches {{Convert|100|km/h}} in 2 seconds, beating the best commercially available supercar (as of 2014). Riders experience up to 1.7 G's of force during acceleration and up to 4.8 G's throughout the ride.<ref name="Official" /><ref name="BBC News">{{cite web|title=World's fastest rollercoaster: Could you stomach it?|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-11620485|publisher=BBC|accessdate=27 November 2014|author=BBC|date=27 October 2010}}</ref> The roller coaster track is {{Convert|2.2|km|mi|abbr=on}} in length, ranking it 6th in the world for steel roller coasters.<ref name="RCDB">{{cite web|title=Formula Rossa (Ferrari World Abu Dhabi)|url=http://www.rcdb.com/m/4485.htm|publisher=Roller Coaster Database|accessdate=6 July 2010|first=Duane|last=Marden}}</ref><ref name=Intamin>{{cite web|title=Formula Rossa > news > Home > Amusement|url=http://www.intaminworldwide.com/amusement/Home/news/FormulaRossa/tabid/150/language/en-US/Default.aspx|publisher=Intamin Worldwide|accessdate=3 February 2011}}</ref> Its shape was inspired by the legendary Italian racetrack [[Autodromo Nazionale Monza]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Borel|first=Brooke|title=How It Works: The World's Fastest Rollercoaster|url=http://www.popsci.com/technology/article/2011-03/how-it-works-worlds-fastest-rollercoaster|publisher=[[popsci.com]]|accessdate=2011-04-03|date=2011-03-31}}</ref> Due to the high air speeds and thus risk of an impact with airborne particulates or [[insect]]s, all riders are required to wear protective glasses similar to those used during [[skydiving]]. Formula Rossa surpassed [[Kingda Ka]] at [[Six Flags Great Adventure]] as the world's fastest roller coaster<ref name="Ferrari - Making of Video">{{cite web|title=Formula Rossa - Making of|url=http://www.ferrari.com/English/Ferrari_TV/Pages/FerrariTVPlayer.aspx?serverId=15856&c=Video|work=Video|publisher=Ferrari|accessdate=6 July 2010|author=Ferrari World}}</ref><ref name="FW Video">{{cite web|title=The making of Formula Rossa|url=http://ferrariworldabudhabi.com/video_player.swf?width=525&height=305&vid=images/video_galleries/fw4to3.flv|publisher=Ferrari World|accessdate=6 July 2010|author=Ferrari World}}</ref> with Kingda Ka retaining the record of the tallest roller coaster in the world.<ref>{{cite RCDB|coaster_name=Record Holders|location=Tallest Roller Coasters|accessdate=1 August 2011|url=http://www.rcdb.com/m/rhr.htm?m=1}}</ref>
In its planning stage it was called '''F1 Coaster'''.
Immediately following the launch, the train ascends a {{Convert|52|m|ft|abbr=on}} hill and eventually completes the course reaching a maximum speed of {{Convert|239|km/h}}.
[[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]] [[Formula One]] drivers [[Felipe Massa]] and [[Fernando Alonso]] rode Formula Rossa on 11 November 2010, three days before the [[2010 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]]. In 2014, Alonso and new teammate [[Kimi Räikkönen]] rode the coaster,<ref>{{cite news|last=Bezants|first=Jack|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2847474/Kimi-Raikkonen-left-unimpressed-planet-s-fastest-rollercoaster-Ferrari-World-Abu-Dhabi.html|title=Kimi Raikkonen left unimpressed after taking on the planet's fastest rollercoaster at Ferrari World in Abu Dhabi|newspaper=[[Daily Mail]]|date=24 November 2014|accessdate=30 November 2015}}</ref> while Räikkönen and [[Sebastian Vettel]] rode in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Luke|url=http://motorsports.nbcsports.com/2015/11/27/vettel-raikkonen-take-on-worlds-fastest-rollercoaster-in-abu-dhabi-video/|title=Vettel, Raikkonen take on world’s fastest rollercoaster in Abu Dhabi (VIDEO)|publisher=[[NBC Sports]]|date=27 November 2015|accessdate=30 November 2015}}</ref>
